Additionally, the switch's lifespan is concerning, with customers noting it randomly cycles on and off repeatedly.

  • hsb1953
    5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    Such a Convenience!!!
    Reviewed in the United States on February 16, 2022
    I purchased two of these smart switches to control our front porch lights and front post lights. Before getting these, we would leave those lights on whenever we traveled. We worried, though, that someone seeing them on during the day might conclude we were gone.... See more
    I purchased two of these smart switches to control our front porch lights and front post lights. Before getting these, we would leave those lights on whenever we traveled. We worried, though, that someone seeing them on during the day might conclude we were gone.

    When they arrived, one of the boxes appeared damaged in shipment. I installed both, and sure enough, one smart switch worked like a champ, and the other one would always operate from the WIFI app, but frequently did not work on the scheduled operation. I notified the seller with pictures of the damaged box, and they shipped a replacement. With the replacement installed, they both now normally operate perfectly.

    I give it five stars for normally working perfectly. They always work manually and with the WIFI app. However, less than 5% of the time one of them (either of them; there is no pattern) won't turn off or on by the schedule. I have them set to go on at 6pm and off at 7am (which I will adjust as the seasons require). I addressed that by modifying the schedules to turn on at 6pm and 6:01pm and turn off at 7am and 7:01am. Since making that change, they have always been working on schedule. For the record, when you are away, you can use the app to ensure that the switches are off or on.

    Both of these switches were installed in the same gang junction box. Their size should accommodate anyone's needs.

    Worse than junk!
    Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2023

    Every switch and plug in my home is a smart one and have been for years. Insteon was the best ubtil they went under and the hub failed, causing me to replace ALL of my wall switches at once. Given the expense of the mass replace, I tried the treatlife switches. I liked... See more
    Every switch and plug in my home is a smart one and have been for years. Insteon was the best ubtil they went under and the hub failed, causing me to replace ALL of my wall switches at once. Given the expense of the mass replace, I tried the treatlife switches. I liked them, except for the fact they had a failure rate of about 50% after just a couple of weeks. I then went to Kasa/TP-Link - reliable, easy to install, but the dimmers only dim in about 5 increments and can be erratic. So, when I decided to replace my last non-smart wall dimmer switch (I had held off because it is a toggle switch and it shares a box and double wall plate with 2 other toggle switches, which are together, but one on top of the other, requiring a special wall plate So, not wanting to buy a hub for just one switch, I went with this one, apparently from SmartLife/Tuya. As my house is entirely "smart", I've gained extensive experience at the installation of all switches, plugs and devices. Plus, I have a 1.2 gig internet connection with unbelievable wifi. This new switch was to be installed within about 4 feet of my router. Of course, it required it's own SmartLife app. First problem/concern arose when I went to use the app to install it and the toggle dimmer was not listed in the app, only the paddle dimmer and they are vastly different, such as the paddle dimmer has a reset button, whiule the toggle dimmer doesn't. Anyway, got it wired easily enough, but then went to program it. First, the switch was almost impossible to get into pairing mode and would keep dropping out of pairing mode. The instructions then made some reference to using two cell phones and setting up a mobile hotspot between the two, etc. It aslo referred to having to perform a reset, using the non-existent reset button and getting the switch to flash blue, which it wouldn't- only orange. The written instructions do not match the app, the app deosn't match the switch, the whole thing is pure junk. All other swirtches have taken maybe 10 minutes to completely install, program and setup with Alexa. After 2 hours of complete failure, this piece of junk went into the trash, not even worth the time, effort or money to send it back. Have ordered a TreatLife paddle to replace it, hoping I get one of the 50% that don't fail and will be customizing my double faceplate to accommodate it. My advice, stay far away from this junk.

  • Steve Birchfield
    5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    A nice replacement for an old style switch
    Reviewed in the United States on March 29, 2024
    Style: Dimmer Switch
    I bought this mainly for 2 reasons. First, it fits in my existing 4 switch box and looks (somewhat) like a normal switch. Also, it uses the Smart Life app which I currently have several other devices under. The install was pretty straight forward if you... See more
    I bought this mainly for 2 reasons. First, it fits in my existing 4 switch box and looks (somewhat) like a normal switch. Also, it uses the Smart Life app which I currently have several other devices under.

    The install was pretty straight forward if you understand wiring for switches. I was using this on a single pole light switch so it was fairly straight forward. I figured out which was load and line then dug out the neutral wire and added that. It all went in like it should and the switch notified me that it was available to add in the app before I could even get there. It connected and worked like it should right away. It's nice having a real switch to use for the lights but also the convenience of a smart switch to turn it on and off as needed. It dims the 4 kitchen lights I have pretty well and is ready for use in Alexa and Google Home.

    The instructions it came with are clear and easy to follow. The company emailed me before I received it and let me know of a change in the instructions, though it didn't affect my installation on a single pole. If you already have some Smart Life apps and want a standard (not decorator style) switch, this is the one to get. We'll see about longevity, but so far I'm happy with it.

    3.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    Does NOT work as a 3-way dimmer switch. Dimmer or 3-way, not both.
    Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2021
    Style: Dimmer Switch
    We bought two WF31TS: the one installed for single-pole operation works well, the 3-way does not. The item description was unclear on limitations: This switch must ALWAYS receive constant hot and neutral, so can only be used as the first switch from the electrical panel in... See more
    We bought two WF31TS: the one installed for single-pole operation works well, the 3-way does not. The item description was unclear on limitations: This switch must ALWAYS receive constant hot and neutral, so can only be used as the first switch from the electrical panel in a standard 3-way (or 4-way) configuration; Option 1 in the instruction manual did not work, only Option 2. Special wiring may be needed for other 3-way switch configurations. The dimming functionality only worked reliably on a simple (1-way) switch configuration, and did not work when wired up as a 3-way switch - which makes it useless for our application. It dimmed the lights during setup and the first operation after the breaker is turned on, but traveler operation instantly reverts it to 100% brightness, and dimming commands seem to only confuse it. If you want a smart dimming 3-way switch, do not buy a WF31TS! As a one-way switch, it works pretty well, though. Smart integration was pretty good with Alexa; it had to be set up using the Smart Life app, but once configured was easy to link to Alexa as a skill. One Smart Life account can be linked to multiple Alexa accounts. Manual operation via the toggle switch is easy and intuitive: one flick to turn on/off, long hold to dim up/down. The color-coded status LED is intuitive as well (white to see it in the dark when lights are off, blue for bluetooth setup, red for wifi problem, green for wifi connected). The slider switch on the bottom was not as intuitive: it's an air-break maintenance switch and should always be in the right-hand position during normal operation. I can't be sure if it's the switch or the bulbs, but harmonics during low-dim operation cause flickering interference with other dimmed lights in the house. The switch seems physically well made, and the terminals were very easy to use. Would have been 5 stars if this was sold as a 1-way smart dimmer switch, but it's only a 1-star 3-way dimmer switch, because it's not a 3-way dimmer switch.

    5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    GREAT but beware you may get a bad one and need to replace it to get expected functionality
    Reviewed in the United States on February 28, 2022
    0:49
    So I finally bit the bullet and decided it was time to upgrade my home automation from legacy X10 to Google Home Automation using WiFi. Purchased a variety of products from Govee, Tuya, Gosund, and others. All join WiFi no problem, some program better than others, but... See more
    So I finally bit the bullet and decided it was time to upgrade my home automation from legacy X10 to Google Home Automation using WiFi. Purchased a variety of products from Govee, Tuya, Gosund, and others. All join WiFi no problem, some program better than others, but this one while it works has a quirk that drives me nuts. It appears when ever WiFi or the Internet is down they start flashing ON-OFF. Like others reported no fun when your bedroom light starts flashing at 2AM. I have 8 of these switches installed and have found if I reboot my Cable Modem router not all but most will start flickering, 5 seconds on 5 seconds off until WiFi/INET is restored. I've been gone on business trips and neighbors report my front porch light or my kitchen light is seen flashing while I'm gone. Tuya Smartlife app is great with this switch for building scenes and controlling them from a toggle switch but this flashing has to stop or I'm gonna find another vendor's product! Subtle but one thing I do like about these Toggle switches is the back lighting makes them easy to see in the dark.....

    UPDATE: I have nine of these switches installed in my home and some of them would flash continuously when the connection to the Internet was lost. My service provider was doing firmware updates at night to my cable modem and my bedroom lights would start flashing continuously at 2AM for 15 minutes until the firmware update completed. Totally frustrated I lashed out at the support team and they admitted this would happen when INET connectivity is lost but only on some switches which they considered a bad batch, not normal behavior. They sent me 3 new switches I installed them and then tested the theory by disconnecting my cable modem.....sure enough the flashing stopped for my bedroom lights and pantry. I walked around the house and found two more switches flashing upstairs so I asked them to send me two more and BOOM now they are behaving as everyone expects. My problem was not a WiFi connectivity problem that the support team kept suggesting. I increased my rating to 5 stars now that all the problems have been resolved.
